[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring a libFuzzer run of the `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`, the Jazzer sanitizer [0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApache Tika CLI “untar” functionality on a crafted input, causing an extracted file[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath to escape the intended extraction directory.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What the issue is  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m drives the Apache Tika `TikaUntar` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCLI class to unpack archive inputs. While processing a specially crafted tar [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive, Jazzer’s FilePathTraversal sanitizer flagged an attempt to write files [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutside the designated extraction directory, leading to a security sanitizer [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  File path traversal: the unpacking code accepts archive entries containing path [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that allow an attacker-controlled archive to place files [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrarily on the filesystem.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations and findings  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The crash stack trace pinpoints the sanitizer hook in [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FilePathTraversal.check` and `FilePathTraversal.pathFirstArgHook`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The vulnerable path is reported as [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mexpander-tmp[0m[39m…[0m[35m/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`, indicating the extraction code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdid not properly sanitize or constrain entry names.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Instrumentation shows that Apache Commons Compress’s TAR input stream and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelated I/O utilities are actively used by `TikaUntar`.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Jazzer loaded a large number of security and coverage hooks, but the critical [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailure is triggered by file-path checks in the Tika untar pathway.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate for a holistic view  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` harness code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry point[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – to understand how inputs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare passed to `TikaUntar`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar` – the main CLI class responsible for tar [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Archive handling in Apache Commons Compress, especially [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TarArchiveInputStream` and any utility methods that construct filesystem paths.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Path normalization and boundary checks in any helper or utility classes that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandle output directories.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Interaction between Tika’s extraction logic and the filesystem, to see where [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitization could be applied or is missing.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn OSS-Fuzz run on the `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` targeting [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar` uncovered a “File path traversal” security [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer violation triggered by extracting entries with paths like [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`q/r/jazzer-traversal`. The initial issue log shows a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom Jazzer’s `FilePathTraversal` hook. A patch was applied to `TikaUntar.java` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat resolves the extracted entry name to an absolute normalized path and throws an[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOException` if the target path escapes the intended extraction directory. After [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the fuzzer still reports a crash—this time a [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.lang.RuntimeException` caused by the newly thrown `IOException: File path [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal detected: ..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer was invoked with `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m` and ran `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` under[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer instrumentation of the Tika untar logic.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During fuzzing, an instrumentation hook [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FilePathTraversal.pathFirstArgHook`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflagged a traversal attempt [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mexpander-tmp[0m[39m…[0m[35m/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and threw a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The log shows the sanitizer detecting a path traversal in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main` when processing a crafted tar entry name.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run ends with a non-zero exit [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstatus [0m[1;36m77[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and writes a Java [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproducer.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Important Observations in the Initial Log**  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Jazzer loaded numerous sanitizers, including FilePathTraversal.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack trace pinpoints `FilePathTraversal.check` and [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pathFirstArgHook` layered into `TikaUntar.main` at line [0m[1;36m47[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness method `parseOne` in `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer` then propagates the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer exception.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File modified: `tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaUntar.java` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround line [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original extraction logic:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patched extraction logic:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                             [0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                             [0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Path destDir = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdestDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal detected: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This adds an explicit check for path traversal and throws `IOException` with a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcustom message when a tar entry’s resolved path does not remain within [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`extractDir`.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Log After Applying the Patch**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer setup and instrumentation logs are largely unchanged.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On running the same testcase, the patch’s traversal check fires on a filename [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlike `..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`, causing an `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mdetected: ../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This `IOException` is wrapped in a `RuntimeException` inside [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne` and surfaces as a fuzzer crash:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Caused by: java.io.IOException: File path traversal detected: [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m..[0m[35m/../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The exit status remains non-zero [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m77[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and a new Java reproducer is emitted.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between `TikaUntar.main` throwing `IOException` and the fuzz [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run on the TikaUntar CLI command triggered a security sanitizer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception reporting “File path traversal.” The initial log shows Jazzer detecting a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical FilePathTraversal issue in `TikaUntar.main` when extracting a tar entry [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhose name leads to an out-of-directory path [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`jazzer-traversal`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A patch was [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplied to `TikaUntar.java` that adds normalization to absolute paths and a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`startsWith` check against the extraction directory, throwing an `IOException` if a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal is detected. After applying the patch, the fuzzer still fails: it now [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrows the injected `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal detected: ..."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msurfaces as a runtime exception in the fuzzer harness.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Jazzer instrumentation and libFuzzer setup complete successfully, loading [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumerous sanitizers including FilePathTraversal.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During a fuzz iteration, an entry name in the test tar triggers [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/.../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace points to [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaUntar.jav[0m[1;92ma:47[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and onward into the harness[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `TikaAppUntarringFuzzer.parseOne` and `fuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run aborts with exit status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m, indicating a sanitizer-triggered [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `TikaUntar.java`, around line [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m, the code that resolves the target path [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor each `TarArchiveEntry` was modified:  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` became `target = [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A new `destDir` is computed as `[0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • An `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdestDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check is added, throwing `new [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal detected: "[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when violated.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The loop continues to create parent directories and write file contents only [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen the check passes.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Log After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer initialization and instrumentation logs remain similar.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On running with the same testcase, the added check triggers an [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal detected: ../../jazzer-traversal"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This exception bubbles up through the harness: first as [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`InvocationTargetException` in `parseOne`, then as `java.lang.RuntimeException: [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msomething went very, very wrong` in `fuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The run still ends with exit status [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m, now due to the forced exception rather[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan the sanitizer.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaAppUntarringFuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arose when the Jazzer-based fuzzer reported a critical “File path[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal” security violation during the unpacking of tar entries in the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaUntar` CLI class. The failure originated from the `FilePathTraversal` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer detecting that an extracted file path escaped the intended target [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory. In response, a patch was applied to normalize and convert both the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction directory and candidate file paths to absolute paths, then skip any [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries whose resolved path did not start with the extraction directory. After [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying this patch, the fuzzer no longer triggered the path traversal sanitizer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut instead hung on the same test input until reaching a [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m-second timeout.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m runs the `TikaUntar` CLI on a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrafted `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m` file.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During execution, Jazzer loads sanitizers and instruments Tika and Commons [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIO/Compress classes.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The run ends with  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal: [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mexpander-tmp[0m[39m*[0m[35m/output/q/r/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      at [0m[1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      at [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.cli.TikaUntar.main[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaUntar.jav[0m[1;92ma:47[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates that the code resolves tar entry names in such a way that entries [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlike `..[0m[35m/../etc/[0m[95mpasswd[0m[39m` can escape the intended extract directory.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `TikaUntar.java`, within the loop over `TarArchiveEntry tae`, the original [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline:  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Was replaced with:  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Path target = [0m[1;35mextractDir.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtae.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Path destDir = [0m[1;35mextractDir.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdestDir[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m skip entries that would extract outside the target directory[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      continue;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This ensures both `target` and `extractDir` are absolute and normalized, and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskips entries where `target` would lie outside `destDir`.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch was applied and the fuzzer re-run under identical conditions.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The path traversal sanitizer no longer triggered.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Instead, the run stalled on the same input and timed out after [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m seconds:  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ALARM: working on the last Unit for [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m seconds[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         and the timeout value is [0m[1;36m25[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  == ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout after [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m seconds[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Thread dumps show the main fuzzing thread stuck during the tar extraction loop [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout producing further sanitizer violations or crashes.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The extraction loop in `TikaUntar.main`, focusing on handling of large or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaliciously structured archives that may cause hangs or performance degradation.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The logic around streaming and skipping entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., early `continue`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether resources [0m[1;39m([0m[39minput streams, iterators[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are properly advanced or closed.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between the fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TikaAppUntarringFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the [0m        [2m                [0m
